arctgz(7)						Miscellaneous Information Manual					      arctgz(7)

NAME
       arctgz - safety-first project lifecycle library for the arctgz archive format

SYNOPSIS
       use arctgz::{
	   init, load_config, save_config,
	   compile, extract, verify,
	   load_recipe, extract_recipe, execute_recipe,
	   ArctgzConfig, ArctgzManifest, FileEntry,
	   ArctgzRecipe, RecipeStep, Compression, ArctgzError
       };
       use std::path::Path;

       fn init(project_path: &Path, force: bool) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn load_config(project_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzConfig, ArctgzError>;
       fn save_config(project_path: &Path, config: &ArctgzConfig) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn compile(
	   project_path: &Path,
	   output_dir: Option<&Path>,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<PathBuf, ArctgzError>;
       fn extract(
	   archive_path: &Path,
	   output_dir: &Path,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn verify(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn load_recipe(project_path: &Path) -> Result<Option<ArctgzRecipe>, ArctgzError>;
       fn extract_recipe(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzRecipe, ArctgzError>;
       fn execute_recipe(
	   output_dir: &Path,
	   recipe: &ArctgzRecipe,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;

       struct ArctgzConfig {
	   pub name:	    String,
	   pub version:	    String,
	   pub include:	    Vec<String>,
	   pub compression: Compression,
       }

       struct ArctgzManifest {
	   pub name:	    String,
	   pub version:	    String,
	   pub created:	    DateTime<Utc>,
	   pub compression: Compression,
	   pub files:	    BTreeMap<String, FileEntry>,
       }

       struct FileEntry {
	   pub size:   u64,
	   pub sha512: String,
       }

       struct ArctgzRecipe {
	   pub name:	String,
	   pub version: String,
	   pub steps:	Vec<RecipeStep>,
       }

       enum RecipeStep {
	   Copy	  { from: String, to: String },
	   MkDir  { path: String },
	   Chmod  { path: String, mode: String },
	   Remove { path: String },
       }

       enum Compression {
	   Gzip,
	   Zstd,
       }

       enum ArctgzError { ... }

DESCRIPTION
       The arctgz library provides a safe, cross-platform API for the full lifecycle of an arctgz project: scaffolding, configuration, compila‐
       tion  into  a compressed and integrity-verified archive, verified extraction, standalone verification, and post-extraction recipe execu‐
       tion.

       All operations enforce strict path confinement, validate metadata before touching the filesystem, and use atomic file operations to pre‐
       vent corruption and TOCTOU (time-of-check to time-of-use) races.

       The core functionality includes:

       • init() – scaffold a new project directory with a default configuration and an empty resource folder.

       • load_config() / save_config() – read and write validated project configuration.

       • compile() – create a compressed archive (gzip or zstd) with SHA-512 hashes and a manifest; supports parallel hashing via rayon.

       • extract() – unpack an archive with full integrity checks and path traversal prevention.

       • verify() – check archive integrity without writing files.

       • load_recipe() / extract_recipe() / execute_recipe() – manage and execute post-extraction recipes (copy, mkdir, chmod, remove).

       All paths are resolved with std::fs::canonicalize() (equivalent to realpath(3)), so symbolic links are followed during  the  home-direc‐
       tory confinement check.	The library is fully tested on Linux, macOS, and Windows.

INSTALLATION
       This man page can be installed system-wide using the provided installer script:

       curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash

       The script places arctgz.7 into /usr/local/share/man/man7/ and updates the man database.	 To uninstall, run:

       curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash -s -- uninstall

FUNCTIONS
       init(project_path, force)
	      Initialises a new arctgz project at project_path.

	      Arguments:

		     project_path
			    A  reference  to  a std::path::Path.  The path must not be empty and must reside (after canonicalisation) under the
			    current user's home directory.  If the path does not exist, it will be created; otherwise it must be a directory.

		     force  If true, skip the non-empty directory check.  However, an existing arctgz.init file will still cause an AlreadyIni‐
			    tialized error.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(()) on success, or an ArctgzError describing the failure.

	      Side effects (only after all safety checks pass):

		     • Creates the project directory (and parents, if needed).

		     • Creates the include/ subdirectory.

		     • Writes a default arctgz.init configuration file atomically (using create_new(true)).  The default configuration includes
		       "compression": "gzip".

	      Security checks (performed before any filesystem modification):

		     • Home directory confinement – the canonicalised project path must start with the canonicalised home  directory.	Symlink
		       attacks are neutralised.

		     • Path validity – rejects empty paths, and rejects existing files (as opposed to directories).

		     • Directory emptiness (unless force is true).

       load_config(project_path)
	      Reads and validates the arctgz.init file from the given project directory.

	      Arguments:

		     project_path
			    Path to the project root (must contain an arctgz.init file).

	      Return value:
		     Ok(ArctgzConfig) if the file exists, contains valid JSON, and passes validate().  On failure, returns an ArctgzError vari‐
		     ant (ConfigNotFound, ConfigLoadError, or ConfigValidation).

       save_config(project_path, config)
	      Writes a validated ArctgzConfig back to the project's arctgz.init file atomically.  The operation first writes the JSON to a tem‐
	      porary file (arctgz.tmp) and then renames it over the original.  This prevents corruption if the process crashes mid-write.

	      Arguments:

		     project_path
			    Path to the project root.

		     config An ArctgzConfig instance to save.  Must pass validate() before saving.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(()) on success, or an ArctgzError (ConfigValidation, ConfigSaveError, or Json).

       compile(project_path, output_dir, force)
	      Compiles the project into an .artgz archive.

	      The function:

	      • Loads the project configuration via load_config().

	      • Collects  the  arctgz.init  file and all files listed in the include array, recursively adding directories while rejecting sym‐
		bolic links.  An optional recipe.json is also included if present.

	      • Computes SHA-512 hashes for every file in parallel using rayon.

	      • Embeds an ArctgzManifest as manifest.json.

	      • Compresses the tar stream with the configured algorithm (Compression::Gzip or Compression::Zstd).

	      • Writes the archive atomically via a temporary file and rename.

	      Arguments:

		     project_path
			    Path to the project root.

		     output_dir
			    Optional output directory.	If None, the archive is placed in project_path/dist/.

		     force  If true, overwrite an existing archive; otherwise fail if the archive already exists.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(PathBuf) containing the full path to the created archive, or an ArctgzError (including IncludeFileNotFound,  SymlinkNo‐
		     tAllowed, RecipeInvalid, or Io for an already-existing archive when force is false).

	      Safety:

		     • Symlinks are rejected to prevent reference leaks outside the project.

		     • If a recipe.json is present, it is validated before compilation; invalid recipes cause RecipeInvalid.

		     • The entire archive is written atomically; a crash mid-write leaves no partial archive.

       extract(archive_path, output_dir, force)
	      Extracts	a  previously  compiled arctgz archive with full integrity verification.  Compression (gzip/zstd) is detected automati‐
	      cally.

	      The function:

	      • Opens and decompresses the archive.

	      • Reads the embedded manifest.json and validates it.

	      • Checks each file path using is_safe_archive_path (rejects absolute paths, .., empty strings, and .).

	      • Verifies that all files in the manifest are present and vice versa.

	      • Hashes each file and compares against the manifest; any mismatch aborts with ChecksumMismatch and removes the partially written
		file.

	      • Writes files to output_dir, creating subdirectories as needed, and refuses to overwrite existing files unless force is true.

	      Arguments:

		     archive_path
			    Path to the .artgz archive.

		     output_dir
			    Destination directory; will be created if it does not exist.

		     force  If true, overwrite existing files; otherwise abort on conflict.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(()) on success, or an ArctgzError (ManifestNotFound, ChecksumMismatch, ExtractError for unsafe paths, or  Io  for  file
		     conflicts).

       verify(archive_path)
	      Standalone  integrity  check.  Reads the archive, validates every file's hash and size against the manifest, ensures all manifest
	      entries are present, and checks for unsafe paths.	 No files are written.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(()) if the archive is valid, or an ArctgzError (ManifestNotFound, ChecksumMismatch for hash or size mismatch, VerifyEr‐
		     ror for missing/extra files or unsafe paths).

       load_recipe(project_path)
	      Loads and validates recipe.json from a project directory.	 Returns Ok(None) if the file does not exist.

       extract_recipe(archive_path)
	      Extracts and validates the embedded recipe.json from an archive.	Automatically detects compression format (gzip or  zstd).   Re‐
	      turns RecipeNotFound if the recipe is missing.

       execute_recipe(output_dir, recipe, force)
	      Runs the steps of a recipe inside output_dir.  Supported steps:

		     Copy { from, to }
			    Copy a file or directory.

		     MkDir { path }
			    Create a directory.

		     Chmod { path, mode }
			    Set Unix permissions (octal string).  On non-Unix platforms this step returns RecipeExecutionError and halts execu‐
			    tion.

		     Remove { path }
			    Delete a file or directory.

	      All  recipe  paths  are validated: absolute paths, .., empty strings, and . are rejected.	 When force is false, existing files or
	      directories cause an error.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(()) on success, or an ArctgzError (RecipeInvalid, RecipeExecutionError).

TYPES
       ArctgzConfig
	      Project configuration stored in arctgz.init.

	      name   Project name (alphanumeric, -, _; max 255 chars).

	      version
		     Semantic version string.

	      include
		     List of relative resource paths (max 100 entries, no .. or absolute paths).

	      compression
		     Compression algorithm: "gzip" (default) or "zstd".

       The configuration file is JSON with #[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]; unknown keys cause a deserialisation error.

       ArctgzManifest
	      Embedded in every archive as manifest.json.

	      name, version
		     Copied from config.

	      created
		     UTC timestamp of compilation.

	      compression
		     Algorithm used for this archive.

	      files  BTreeMap from archive paths to FileEntry.

       FileEntry
	      Metadata for one file: size (u64) and sha512 hex string.

       ArctgzRecipe
	      Describes post-extraction actions.

	      name, version
		     Recipe identity.

	      steps  Ordered list of RecipeStep.

       RecipeStep
	      Enum with Copy, MkDir, Chmod, Remove.

       Compression
	      Enum: Gzip (default), Zstd.

       ArctgzError
	      All failure variants, including:

	      RecipeNotFound
		     Recipe not found in archive.

	      RecipeInvalid
		     Recipe validation failed.

	      RecipeExecutionError
		     Recipe step could not be performed.

	      VerifyError
		     Verification failed (missing file, size mismatch, unsafe path, etc.).

EXAMPLE
   Initialising a project with zstd compression
       use arctgz::{init, load_config, save_config, Compression};

       fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
	   let project = Path::new("./my-project");
	   init(project, false)?;
	   let mut cfg = load_config(project)?;
	   cfg.compression = Compression::Zstd;
	   save_config(project, &cfg)?;
	   Ok(())
       }

   Compile, verify, and extract with a recipe
       use arctgz::{compile, verify, extract, execute_recipe, extract_recipe};

       fn build_and_deploy(project: &Path) -> Result<(), arctgz::ArctgzError> {
	   let archive = compile(project, None, false)?;
	   verify(&archive)?;
	   let out_dir = Path::new("/tmp/deploy");
	   extract(&archive, out_dir, true)?;
	   let recipe = extract_recipe(&archive)?;
	   execute_recipe(out_dir, &recipe, true)?;
	   Ok(())
       }

   Example recipe.json
       {
	 "name": "setup",
	 "version": "1.0.0",
	 "steps": [
	   { "action": "mkdir", "path": "logs" },
	   { "action": "copy", "from": "default.cfg", "to": "config.cfg" },
	   { "action": "chmod", "path": "bin/app", "mode": "755" },
	   { "action": "remove", "path": "temp.txt" }
	 ]
       }

FILES
       arctgz.init
	      Project configuration (JSON).  The file is strictly validated; unknown fields cause an error.  Written atomically by  init()  and
	      save_config().

       include/
	      Resource directory.

       dist/<name>-<version>.artgz
	      Default archive output (gzip or zstd).

       recipe.json (optional)
	      Post-extraction recipe embedded into the archive.

ENVIRONMENT
       HOME (Unix) / USERPROFILE (Windows)
	      The  library  obtains  the current user's home directory through the dirs crate.	On Unix, the HOME variable is used; on Windows,
	      USERPROFILE.  If the appropriate variable is not set, a platform-specific fallback is attempted.	If no home directory can be de‐
	      termined, init() will fail with PathNotAllowed for any path (even relative ones) because confinement cannot be verified.

SECURITY
       • Path confinement: only paths inside the canonicalised home directory are allowed for initialisation.  Symlink traversal is fully miti‐
	 gated by canonicalising both the project path and the home directory.

       • No side effects before validation: init() resolves the path and performs all security checks before creating any  directories.	  Thus,
	 even a failed call with a path outside the home directory will not leave unwanted directories on disk.

       • Atomic	 writes: the use of create_new(true) for init(), and temp file + rename for save_config() and compile(), ensure the target file
	 is never left in an incomplete state.

       • Archive integrity: every file in the archive is hashed with SHA-512.  The manifest is embedded and verified during extraction and ver‐
	 ification; any hash or size mismatch aborts with ChecksumMismatch.

       • Path traversal prevention: extract() and verify() reject archive paths that are absolute, contain .., are empty, or equal ..  The same
	 validation applies to recipe paths.

       • Symlink rejection: compile() refuses to include symbolic links, ensuring archives contain only regular files and directories.

       • Input validation: configuration and recipe fields are strictly validated.  Unknown JSON keys are rejected,  preventing	 accidental  or
	 malicious settings from entering the project metadata.

NOTES
       The library is intended to be used as a building block for higher-level tools.  It does not impose any locking mechanism; concurrent op‐
       erations	 on  the same project directory may lead to races.  However, each individual write operation (config save, archive creation) is
       atomic, so partial corruption is avoided even under concurrent access.  Users should serialise access when multiple processes or threads
       operate on the same project.

VERSION
       arctgz 0.6.0 – introduces robust manifest reading via read_manifest, improved path safety checks	 (is_safe_archive_path),  and  corrects
       the behaviour of Chmod on non-Unix platforms to return an error instead of silently doing nothing.

SEE ALSO
       semver(7), realpath(3), serde_json(5), dirs(7), flate2(7), zstd(1), tar(5), sha2(7), rayon(7)

BUGS
       • The include/ directory is always created empty; files must be added manually before compilation.

       • Concurrent  operations	 on the same project directory are not serialised; while individual writes are atomic, the overall state may be
	 inconsistent if multiple processes write simultaneously.

       • No cryptographic signatures yet; integrity relies solely on SHA-512 hashes.

       • The Chmod step is not supported on non-Unix platforms and will return an error.

